abstract: “How is this the first we’re hearing of Michael Avenatti’s racecar team?” the “Late Night” host said after the lawyer’s indictment was made public on Thursday.

abstract: A surprising, important difference between the Green New Deal and Medicare for all.
snippet: A surprising, important difference between the Green New Deal and Medicare for all.
lead_paragraph: Right now there are two big progressive ideas out there: the Green New Deal on climate change and “Medicare for all” on health reform. Both would move U.S. policy significantly to the left. Each is sponsored by a self-proclaimed socialist: the Green New Deal by Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and Medicare for all by Bernie Sanders. (Of course, neither of them is a socialist in the traditional sense.) Both ideas horrify not just conservatives but also many self-proclaimed centrists.

abstract: The poll, conducted by Monmouth University, also indicated that support for Mayor Pete Buttigieg is on the rise.
snippet: The poll, conducted by Monmouth University, also indicated that support for Mayor Pete Buttigieg is on the rise.
lead_paragraph: Despite a turbulent week in which he was accused by several women of inappropriate physical contact, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. remains popular among Iowa Democrats and leads a new poll that also indicates Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., is on the rise.

abstract: The Vermont socialist is suddenly rich. Is he any wiser?
snippet: The Vermont socialist is suddenly rich. Is he any wiser?
lead_paragraph: “I wrote a best-selling book. If you write a best-selling book, you can be a millionaire, too.” With those insouciant words, Bernie Sanders acknowledged on Tuesday that he has joined the ranks of the “millionaires and billionaires” he has vilified for most of his career.
